10d3			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
10d3			 
10d3			; String Length 
10d3			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
10d3			 
10d3			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
10d3			;    LD     HL, $8000 
10d3			 
10d3			strlenz: 
10d3			 
10d3 af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
10d4 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
10d5 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
10d6			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
10d6 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
10d8			 
10d8			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
10d8 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
10d9 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
10da ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
10dc 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
10dd c9				ret 
10de			 
10de			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
10de			;    LD     HL, $8000 
10de			 
10de			strlent: 
10de			 
10de			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
10de 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
10e0 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
10e2			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
10e2 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
10e4			 
10e4			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
10e4 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
10e6 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
10e8 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
10ea 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
10eb c9				ret 
